properties.ABOUT: The community garden serves several purposes. It provides a space for the community to gather and share; the heart of the garden features a friendship garden where everything grown is freely shared. The garden also addresses the nutritional and health needs of the community and seeks to teach people about self-sufficiency and how they can grow their own food at the garden and in their own homes.
